
A minimal example for calling a C function via cython.

Build an example C program using the Makefile

Otherwise:
 python setup.py build_ext --inplace
 python test_cython_interface.py
 python test_cffi_interface.py
 python test_f2py_interface.py

... conclusions ?
 - cython looks good, but new language and heavy c output
 - f2py appears to work fine. Only uses the C compiler for C.
 - ffi worked but needed a python wrapper to do a cast + from_buffer
 - opencl is clunky / slower due to copies



